# Perforce MCP Server Setup

This repository provides MCP servers for Perforce + Swarm integration with Cursor IDE.

## When user asks to "set up" or "install" this project:

Run the setup script:
```bash
chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh
```

The setup script handles EVERYTHING from a bare macOS machine:
1. Installs Homebrew (if missing)
2. Installs p4 CLI (if missing)
3. Installs Python 3 (if missing)
4. Installs Node.js (if missing, needed for sequential-thinking MCP)
5. Downloads p4-mcp-server binary (guides user if manual download needed)
6. Installs Python dependencies (fastmcp, httpx)
7. Tests Perforce connectivity
8. Authenticates + saves password to macOS Keychain
9. Generates ~/.cursor/mcp.json with correct paths
10. Installs Cursor AI workflow rules globally

After setup completes, the user must restart Cursor (Cmd+Q, reopen).

## Repository structure:

- `setup.sh` — One-click installer (run this)
- `perforce-p4/p4-mcp-start.sh` — Wrapper for official Perforce MCP server
- `p4-workflow/server.py` — Custom Perforce + Swarm workflow MCP server
- `p4-workflow/requirements.txt` — Python dependencies
- `rules/p4-workflow.mdc` — Cursor AI rules for workflow guidance
- `mcp.json.template` — Manual config reference
